fix: memory hooks were never activated because HooksConfig derived Default which gave empty vecs, and the user's xpressclaw.yaml had explicit 'before_message: []' which overrode any defaults. Made the fields serde(skip) so they always use Default::default() which includes memory_recall and memory_remember. Removed hooks from the config template since they're internal, not user-configurable. The user correctly pointed out that hooks shouldn't be in the YAML if users can't meaningfully configure them.
